  <div class="sec-mark">Why Your Data Is Wrong</div>
  <div class="prose" id="why-data-wrong">
    <h2>Why Your Shopify Conversion Data Is Wrong in 2026</h2>
    <p>For years, Shopify merchants relied on browser pixels &mdash; small JavaScript files that execute in the customer&rsquo;s browser when they reach the thank-you page, sending a Purchase event to Meta, Google, or TikTok. The problem: that browser is increasingly hostile to ad tracking in 2026.</p>
    <p>Apple&rsquo;s Intelligent Tracking Prevention (ITP) prevents the JavaScript your pixel relies on from identifying returning visitors or attributing purchases to earlier ad clicks. Ad blockers intercept pixel scripts before they execute. Users who close the tab before the thank-you page fully loads never fire the pixel at all. Cross-device journeys &mdash; ad viewed on phone, purchase made on desktop &mdash; break attribution entirely.</p>
    <p>The result is a systematic gap between real sales and reported conversions. Your ad campaigns are spending budget optimised against a partial signal &mdash; the algorithm is choosing audiences and bids based on 60&ndash;80% of what actually happened. TikTok&rsquo;s own data shows a <strong>19% average increase in attributed events</strong> when stores implement server-side tracking alongside their browser pixel.</p>
  </div>

