    <span class="callout-label">Shopify Native CAPI Has a Browser Dependency</span>
    <p>Shopify offers &ldquo;Maximum data sharing&rdquo; in customer event settings, and most guides stop there. The problem: Shopify&rsquo;s native CAPI integration is still partially browser-triggered. If the thank-you page pixel doesn&rsquo;t fire due to an ad blocker, a slow connection, or the user navigating away &mdash; the event may not reach your ad platform even with native CAPI enabled. The Make.com webhook method fires from Shopify&rsquo;s server the instant payment confirms, with <strong>zero browser dependency</strong>.</p>
  </div>

