        <div class="step-desc">
          In Shopify Admin, go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Notifications &rarr; Webhooks</strong> and click <strong>Create webhook</strong>. Select <strong>Order payment</strong> as the event, paste your Make.com webhook URL as the destination, set format to JSON, save.
          <br/><br/>Shopify now pushes every paid order to Make.com in real time &mdash; completely independent of browser behaviour. This is the moment your tracking becomes unblockable.
        </div>
        <span class="step-time">&#8987; ~3 minutes</span>
        <span class="step-path">Shopify Admin &rarr; Settings &rarr; Notifications &rarr; Webhooks</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="step-card meta">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">4</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">
          <span class="step-platform-tag spt-meta">Meta CAPI</span>
          Add Meta CAPI HTTP module
        </div>
        <div class="step-desc">
          First, in <strong>Meta Events Manager &rarr; your Pixel &rarr; Settings</strong>, generate a Conversions API Access Token and copy your Pixel ID.
          <br/><br/>Add an HTTP module after the webhook trigger in Make.com. Set Method to POST, URL to <span class="code-ref">https://graph.facebook.com/v19.0/YOUR_PIXEL_ID/events?access_token=YOUR_TOKEN</span>. In the body, send:
          <ul style="margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;">
            <li><span class="code-ref">event_name</span>: Purchase</li>
            <li><span class="code-ref">event_id</span>: <span class="code-ref">&#123;&#123;order.id&#125;&#125;</span></li>
            <li><span class="code-ref">event_time</span>: current Unix timestamp</li>
            <li><span class="code-ref">value</span>: order total &amp; <span class="code-ref">currency</span></li>
            <li><span class="code-ref">em</span>: SHA-256 hashed customer email</li>
          </ul>
          Verify in <strong>Meta Events Manager &rarr; Test Events</strong>. A Purchase event with source &ldquo;server&rdquo; should appear within 60 seconds.
        </div>
        <span class="step-time">&#8987; ~5 minutes</span>
        <span class="step-path">Meta Events Manager &rarr; your Pixel &rarr; Settings &rarr; Conversions API Access Token</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="callout warn">
    <span class="callout-label">Deduplication is Required &mdash; Do Not Skip</span>
    <p>Set <span class="code-ref">event_id</span> to the Shopify order ID in your server event. In your browser Meta Pixel code, also pass <span class="code-ref">eventID: '&#123;&#123;order.id&#125;&#125;'</span> in the Purchase event. Meta uses matching event IDs to deduplicate &mdash; you see one purchase, not two. <strong>Without this, you will double-count every conversion and your ROAS will appear inflated.</strong></p>
