          In <strong>TikTok Ads Manager &rarr; Assets &rarr; Events &rarr; your Pixel &rarr; Settings</strong>, generate an Events API Access Token and copy your Pixel ID.
          <br/><br/>Add a third HTTP module. Set Method to POST, URL to <span class="code-ref">https://business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/event/track/</span>. In the body, include:
          <ul style="margin-top:10px;margin-bottom:10px;">
            <li><span class="code-ref">event_name</span>: <strong>CompletePayment</strong> (not &ldquo;Purchase&rdquo; &mdash; see warning below)</li>
            <li><span class="code-ref">event_id</span>: <span class="code-ref">&#123;&#123;order.id&#125;&#125;</span></li>
            <li>Value, currency, hashed email and phone</li>
            <li>Customer IP address and user agent (from Shopify order payload)</li>
          </ul>
          IP address and user agent are available directly in the Shopify webhook payload and improve Event Match Quality significantly &mdash; include both.
        </div>
        <span class="step-time">&#8987; ~5 minutes</span>
        <span class="step-path">TikTok Ads Manager &rarr; Assets &rarr; Events &rarr; Web Events &rarr; your Pixel &rarr; Settings</span>
