        <span class="step-path">Make.com &rarr; toggle scenario on &rarr; place test order</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="callout tiktok">
    <span class="callout-label">TikTok Uses CompletePayment, Not Purchase</span>
    <p>TikTok uses <strong>CompletePayment</strong> as the purchase event name &mdash; not &ldquo;Purchase&rdquo; like Meta and Google. Using the wrong event name is the most common TikTok CAPI setup error. Events will appear in Events Manager but under the wrong category and will not feed into purchase campaign optimisation. Check this before going live.</p>
